COVID-19 Status 💉 🦠

As of 8:15AM PT today, over 2.7 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 31.2 thousand have died.

In the last day, 18.7 thousand new infections were reported and 80 deaths. Currently 8,613 are in the hospital and 1,026 are in the ICU. This is trending downwards.

Fortunately, 72.7 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 5 years and older, 87.5% have their 1st shot and 80.9% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is speeding up, but there are 7.5 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~24 days for new deliveries to get into arms.

At the current rate, Canadians should achieve herd immunity around when 80% of the entire population is fully vaccinated. There is no approved vaccine for children under 5.

    72 in 100 are fully vaccinated. From storage
    34 in 100 more could receive a dose.
